HEADWORD: Illision
<hw>Il*li"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>illisio</ets>, fr. <ets>illidere</ets>, <ets>illisum</ets>, to
strike against; pref. <ets>il-</ets> in + <ets>laedere</ets> to
strike.]</ety> <def>The act of dashing or striking against.</def>
